CHUKWUJEKWU ILOZUE; RAYMOND OZOJI AWKA  – The police in Anambra State has reported an alleged mur­der case involving one Ozioma Orakwe, aged 27 of Amatutu village Agulu Anaocha Local Government Area of Anam­bra State. A press statement released on the unfortunate incident by the state police spokes­man DSP Ikenga Tochi on Friday has it that the suspect has made useful confessional statements helping the police in the ongoing investigation of the murder of one Mar­tin Orakwe, aged 75 years of Amatutu village Agulu Anao­cha council area over alleged domestic issues. Gunmen Attack Farm Owner In Lagos-Ogun Border OAU Student’s Murder: Court Fixes Full Hearing For Monday The statement reads, “The Commissioner of Police CP Echeng Echeng has admon­ished citizens to always seek other means of settling their differences than resorting to fighting and violence.” The CP gave this counsel while reacting to arrest of one Ozioma Orakwe ‘F’ aged 27years on the alleged murder of Martin Orakwe ‘M’, aged 75years of Amatutu village, Agulu Anaocha LGA. Against the report received on March 2, at 3:08pm from one Mr Sunday Orakwe of alleged suicide by the deceased, pre­liminary investigation reveals that the victim had a cut on his head with marks of violence all over his body. Additional information shows that the suspect, a rel­ative to the deceased, had a disagreement which resulted to a fight. Meanwhile, police opera­tives have recovered the body of the deceased and the sus­pect have also made useful statement that is helping in the ongoing investigation. The case shall be charged to court after a conclusive investigation.